{"action":"created","issue":{"url":"https://api.github.com/repos/JuliaLang/julia/issues/56034","repository_url":"https://api.github.com/repos/JuliaLang/julia","labels_url":"https://api.github.com/repos/JuliaLang/julia/issues/56034/labels{/name}","comments_url":"https://api.github.com/repos/JuliaLang/julia/issues/56034/comments","events_url":"https://api.github.com/repos/JuliaLang/julia/issues/56034/events","html_url":"https://github.com/JuliaLang/julia/pull/56034","id":2571580169,"node_id":"PR_kwDOABkWpM5932JK","number":56034,"title":"array: inline `convert` where possible","user":{"login":"topolarity","id":84105208,"node_id":"MDQ6VXNlcjg0MTA1MjA4","avatar_url":"https://avatars.githubusercontent.com/u/84105208?v=4","gravatar_id":"","url":"https://api.github.com/users/topolarity","html_url":"https://github.com/topolarity","followers_url":"https://api.github.com/users/topolarity/followers","following_url":"https://api.github.com/users/topolarity/following{/other_user}","gists_url":"https://api.github.com/users/topolarity/gists{/gist_id}","starred_url":"https://api.github.com/users/topolarity/starred{/owner}{/repo}","subscriptions_url":"https://api.github.com/users/topolarity/subscriptions","organizations_url":"https://api.github.com/users/topolarity/orgs","repos_url":"https://api.github.com/users/topolarity/repos","events_url":"https://api.github.com/users/topolarity/events{/privacy}","received_events_url":"https://api.github.com/users/topolarity/received_events","type":"User","site_admin":false},"labels":[{"id":62693664,"node_id":"MDU6TGFiZWw2MjY5MzY2NA==","url":"https://api.github.com/repos/JuliaLang/julia/labels/arrays","name":"arrays","color":"006b75","default":false,"description":"[a, r, r, a, y, s]"}],"state":"open","locked":false,"assignee":null,"assignees":[],"milestone":null,"comments":3,"created_at":"2024-10-07T22:02:59Z","updated_at":"2024-10-08T13:25:52Z","closed_at":null,"author_association":"MEMBER","active_lock_reason":null,"draft":false,"pull_request":{"url":"https://api.github.com/repos/JuliaLang/julia/pulls/56034","html_url":"https://github.com/JuliaLang/julia/pull/56034","diff_url":"https://github.com/JuliaLang/julia/pull/56034.diff","patch_url":"https://github.com/JuliaLang/julia/pull/56034.patch","merged_at":null},"body":"This improves a common scenario, where someone wants to `push!` a poorly-typed object onto a well-typed Vector.

For example:
```julia
const NT = @NamedTuple{x::Int,y::Any}
foo(v::Vector{NT}, x::Int, @nospecialize(y)) = push!(v, (; x, y))
```

The `(; x, y)` is slightly poorly-typed here. It could have any type for its `.y` field before it is converted inside the `push!` to a NamedTuple with `y::Any`

Without this PR, the dispatch for this `push!` cannot be inferred:
```julia
julia> code_typed(foo, (Vector{NT}, Int, Any))[1]
 CodeInfo(
1 ─ ...
│   %4 = %new(%3, x, y)::NamedTuple{(:x, :y), <:Tuple{Int64, Any}}
│   %5 = Main.push!(v, %4)::Vector{@NamedTuple{x::Int64, y}}
└──      return %5
) => Vector{@NamedTuple{x::Int64, y}}
```

With this PR, the above dynamic call is fully statically resolved and inlined (and therefore `--trim` compatible)","reactions":{"url":"https://api.github.com/repos/JuliaLang/julia/issues/56034/reactions","total_count":2,"+1":0,"-1":0,"laugh":0,"hooray":0,"confused":0,"heart":2,"rocket":0,"eyes":0},"timeline_url":"https://api.github.com/repos/JuliaLang/julia/issues/56034/timeline","performed_via_github_app":null,"state_reason":null},"comment":{"url":"https://api.github.com/repos/JuliaLang/julia/issues/comments/2399845539","html_url":"https://github.com/JuliaLang/julia/pull/56034#issuecomment-2399845539","issue_url":"https://api.github.com/repos/JuliaLang/julia/issues/56034","id":2399845539,"node_id":"IC_kwDOABkWpM6PCryj","user":{"login":"topolarity","id":84105208,"node_id":"MDQ6VXNlcjg0MTA1MjA4","avatar_url":"https://avatars.githubusercontent.com/u/84105208?v=4","gravatar_id":"","url":"https://api.github.com/users/topolarity","html_url":"https://github.com/topolarity","followers_url":"https://api.github.com/users/topolarity/followers","following_url":"https://api.github.com/users/topolarity/following{/other_user}","gists_url":"https://api.github.com/users/topolarity/gists{/gist_id}","starred_url":"https://api.github.com/users/topolarity/starred{/owner}{/repo}","subscriptions_url":"https://api.github.com/users/topolarity/subscriptions","organizations_url":"https://api.github.com/users/topolarity/orgs","repos_url":"https://api.github.com/users/topolarity/repos","events_url":"https://api.github.com/users/topolarity/events{/privacy}","received_events_url":"https://api.github.com/users/topolarity/received_events","type":"User","site_admin":false},"created_at":"2024-10-08T13:25:52Z","updated_at":"2024-10-08T13:25:52Z","author_association":"MEMBER","body":"> Are you referring to the `@_noub_meta` annotation attached to `insert!(a::Array{T,1}, i::Integer, item)`? I wasn’t the one who added it, but I believe it’s dangerous to apply that annotation to methods that include `convert`, as user-defined types could be provided. Since `insert!(a::Array{T,1}, i::Integer, item::T)` already has `@_noub_meta` applied, I don’t think it’s necessary to add the annotation to `insert!(a::Array{T,1}, i::Integer, item)`.

