 possible","user":{"login":"topolarity","id":84105208,"node_id":"MDQ6VXNlcjg0MTA1MjA4","avatar_url":"https://avatars.githubusercontent.com/u/84105208?v=4","gravatar_id":"","url":"https://api.github.com/users/topolarity","html_url":"https://github.com/topolarity","followers_url":"https://api.github.com/users/topolarity/followers","following_url":"https://api.github.com/users/topolarity/following{/other_user}","gists_url":"https://api.github.com/users/topolarity/gists{/gist_id}","starred_url":"https://api.github.com/users/topolarity/starred{/owner}{/repo}","subscriptions_url":"https://api.github.com/users/topolarity/subscriptions","organizations_url":"https://api.github.com/users/topolarity/orgs","repos_url":"https://api.github.com/users/topolarity/repos","events_url":"https://api.github.com/users/topolarity/events{/privacy}","received_events_url":"https://api.github.com/users/topolarity/received_events","type":"User","site_admin":false},"body":"This improves a common scenario, where someone wants to `push!` a poorly-typed object onto a well-typed Vector.

For example:
```julia
const NT = @NamedTuple{x::Int,y::Any}
foo(v::Vector{NT}, x::Int, @nospecialize(y)) = push!(v, (; x, y))
```

The `(; x, y)` is slightly poorly-typed here. It could have any type for its `.y` field before it is converted inside the `push!` to a NamedTuple with `y::Any`

Without this PR, the dispatch for this `push!` cannot be inferred:
```julia
julia> code_typed(foo, (Vector{NT}, Int, Any))[1]
 CodeInfo(
1 ─ ...
│   %4 = %new(%3, x, y)::NamedTuple{(:x, :y), <:Tuple{Int64, Any}}
│   %5 = Main.push!(v, %4)::Vector{@NamedTuple{x::Int64, y}}
└──      return %5
) => Vector{@NamedTuple{x::Int64, y}}
```

With this PR, the above dynamic call is fully statically resolved and inlined (and therefore `--trim` compatible)","created_at":"2024-10-07T22:02:59Z","updated_at":"2024-10-09T12:57:22Z","closed_at":null,"merged_at":null,"merge_commit_sha":"77f5d8030e7ab2c2054450497a6d63472c3fa96b","assignee":null,"assignees":[],"requested_reviewers":[{"login":"oscardssmith","id":11729272,"node_id":"MDQ6VXNlcjExNzI5Mjcy","avatar_url":"https://avatars.githubusercontent.com/u/11729272?v=4","gravatar_id":"","url":"https://api.github.com/users/oscardssmith","html_url":"https://github.com/oscardssmith","followers_url":"https://api.github.com/users/oscardssmith/followers","following_url":"https://api.github.com/users/oscardssmith/following{/other_user}","gists_url":"https://api.github.com/users/oscardssmith/gists{/gist_id}","starred_url":"https://api.github.com/users/oscardssmith/starred{/owner}{/repo}","subscriptions_url":"https://api.github.com/users/oscardssmith/subscriptions","organizations_url":"https://api.github.com/users/oscardssmith/orgs","repos_url":"https://api.github.com/users/oscardssmith/repos","events_url":"https://api.github.com/users/oscardssmith/events{/privacy}","received_events_url":"https://api.github.com/users/oscardssmith/received_events","type":"User","site_admin":false}],"requested_teams":[],"labels":[{"id":62693664,"node_id":"MDU6TGFiZWw2MjY5MzY2NA==","url":"https://api.github.com/repos/JuliaLang/julia/labels/arrays","name":"arrays","color":"006b75","default":false,"description":"[a, r, r, a, y, s]"}],"milestone":null,"draft":false,"commits_url":"https://api.github.com/repos/JuliaLang/julia/pulls/56034/commits","review_comments_url":"https://api.github.com/repos/JuliaLang/julia/pulls/56034/comments","review_comment_url":"https://api.github.com/repos/JuliaLang/julia/pulls/comments{/number}","comments_url":"https://api.github.com/repos/JuliaLang/julia/issues/56034/comments","statuses_url":"https://api.github.com/repos/JuliaLang/julia/statuses/548cbe20bca5dec70b26fc